h3. Ingredients
* 1 tbs olive oil
* 420g Pork Fillet, thinly sliced across the grain
* 1 bunch broccolini, cut into thirds
* 2 green shallots, ends trimmed, cut into 4cm lengths
* 2 garlic cloves, crushed
* 1 fresh red chilli, halved, deseeded, finely chopped
* 1 tbs finely grated fresh ginger
* 80ml kecap (ketjup) manis
* 2 tbs fresh lime juice
* Steamed rice, to serve
* 1 fresh red chilli, extra, thinly sliced, to serve
* Lime wedges, to serve

h3. Method

# Heat half the oil in a wok over high heat until just smoking. Add half the pork and stir-fry for 3-4 minutes or until brown all over. Transfer to a place. Repeat with the remaining oil and pork, reheating wok between batches.
# Add the broccolini to the wok and stir-fry for 2 minutes or until just tender. Add the pork, green shallot, garlic, chilli and ginger, and stir-fry for 1 minute or until aromatic. Add the kecap manis and lime juice and bring to the boil.
# Spoon the steamed rice among serving bowls. Top with the pork and broccolini stir-fry. Sprinkle with the extra chilli and serve immediately with lime wedges, if desired.

